.TH "nfc_start_poll" 9 "nfc_start_poll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfc_start_poll \- start polling for nfc targets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nfc_start_poll
.BI "(struct nfc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 im_protocols "  ","
.BI "u32 tm_protocols "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
The nfc device that must start polling
.IP "im_protocols" 12
bitset of nfc initiator protocols to be used for polling
.IP "tm_protocols" 12
bitset of nfc transport protocols to be used for polling
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The device remains polling for targets until a target is found or
the nfc_stop_poll function is called.
